Description: As a Druid, flexibility is part of your nature.  These Basic and Classic cards allow you to accelerate ahead of your opponent and to adapt to their strategy as you choose!
Name: Classic Druid

Description: Continuously assault your opponent with the most ferocious beasts Azeroth has to offer. And a few non-beasts. They're honorary beasts.
Name: Ferocious Beasts

Description: What is better than three minions?  Seven, of course! Summon an army of smaller minions, and grow them into huge monsters.
Name: Overwhelming Numbers

Description: Elements guide your path!  Use elemental magic to destroy enemy minions, and enhance your own to overwhelm your opponent.  All you need is Basic and Classic cards!
Name: Classic Shaman

Description: On their own, each totem is fairly weak, but amassing an army of them can be quite scary. It'll help you win the game, too.
Name: Totally Totems

Description: Try rushing down your opponents using the Murloc’s aggressive synergies and finish them off with direct damage.
Name: Murlocs Unleashed

Description: What doesn’t kill us makes us stronger! These Basic and Classic cards take advantage of taking damage, and allow your hero to take part in the battle with weapons!
Name: Classic Warrior

Description: Dealing damage to your own minions is your path to victory here. Keep them alive long enough to take damage multiple times.
Name: Unleash Your Rage

Description: This deck only has one copy of each card in it, so that Reno Jackson can bring you back from the brink!
Name: Reno Jackson

Description: Orchestrate the situation to your maximum advantage.  Exploit card interactions and strike swiftly with this deadly aggressive deck of Basic and Classic cards!
Name: Classic Rogue

Description: Combo multiple cards together in a single turn for maximum effectiveness!  Keep control and pair your cards effectively.
Name: It's Combo Time

Description: Surprise your opponent with just how much damage you can do. Spell Damage minions will strengthen your spells to help finish the job.
Name: Empowered Spells

Description: Interested in justice?  Consider a career as a Paladin with these Basic and Classic cards!  Command your army to control the board and cast blessed spells of the Light!
Name: Classic Paladin

Description: Keep your opponent's board clear and finish the job with your high cost dragons.
Name: Dragons of Justice

Description: Summon the greatest army of the tides. You’ll need to practice your battle cry! All together now: "MRGGLGLGGGL!"
Name: Tide of Murlocs

Description: Wild animals answer your call, as you lay down traps and strike with your bow. Hunt your opponent with this deck of Basic and Classic cards.
Name: Classic Hunter

Description: Set traps to protect yourself as you control the pace with other spells. End the game with some of your bigger minions or a flurry of damage to your opponent’s hero.
Name: Deathtrap

Description: This Hunter deck is one of the most aggressive in the game.  Remember: if you're not attacking their hero, you're probably doing it wrong.
Name: The Thrill of the Hunt

Description: Power is all that matters. Seize it, no matter the cost. This fast paced deck of Basic and Classic cards is full of minions intent on swift destruction of your opponent.
Name: Classic Warlock

Description: Fill your board up and keep it full. Many of your cards become more powerful when you have tons of minions on the field, so decide carefully how your minions attack.
Name: Demon Horde

Description: You’ll want to stay alive while using your Hero Power as much as possible, some of your cards get better the more cards you have in your hand.
Name: Handlock

Description: Want to be a Mage?  This deck of timeless Basic and Classic cards is designed to enhance and support spell casting!
Name: Classic Mage

Description: This deck is packed with tons of minions who find you more cards.  Trade your spells and minions for theirs aggressively to leverage the extra cards you’re getting.
Name: Spells Unending

Description: The ancient dragons will crush all opposition, assuming you live long enough to summon them. Nefarian told me to tell you not to embarrass him by dying.
Name: Dragonfire

Description: Are you a healer?  With this deck of solid Basic and Classic cards, keep your minions alive as they fight for you!
Name: Classic Priest

Description: Take matters into your own hands. Trade in some healing spells for deadly shadow magic and aggressive minions!
Name: Strike With the Shadows

Description: Survival is key when dealing with dragons. If you can last long enough, your big dragons will end up taking over the late game.
Name: Dragonflight

Description: Protect yourself as your devotion to C’Thun grows. Amass enough armor that your opponent’s efforts become futile before the Old Gods!
Name: Serve the Old Gods

Description: Summon as many minions as possible before evolving them! Evolve minions that have already done work for you to maximize your value!
Name: Minion Evolution

Description: Protect your minions with Divine Shield and they’ll be able to take on two enemies at a time!
Name: Shields Up!

Description: Use the Druid’s Mana-generating spells to summon the servants of the Old Gods way ahead of schedule.
Name: The Ancient Gods

Description: Bolster your armies with the innumerable minions of the Old Gods. Swarm the board with smaller minions to overwhelm your opponent.
Name: Ancient Hordes

Description: Trade your minions aggressively! Most of them give you an advantage when they're killed, so sacrifice away.
Name: Echoes of Death

Description: Heal your minions to keep them alive long enough to see the rise of the horrific C’Thun!
Name: C’Thun’s Clutch

Description: Do not fear death, hero; your minions are useful to you both alive and dead. Keep trading your minions for theirs; you will eventually overwhelm them.
Name: Whispers of Death

Description: Cast as many spells as possible: Each one will fuel the reawakening of Yogg-Saron.

Description: Use every trick in the Grimy Goons' playbook to get one up on your opponent. Finish them off with a huge minion you’ve empowered in your hand.
Name: The Goons’ Empire

Description: One of Gadgetzan’s fishier districts plays home to roving groups of Murlocs. Once you get enough of them together, they can overrun the enemy with a well-timed spell.
Name: Murloc Association

Description: The Goons have helped you procure a few… implements. Power up the minions in your hand before sending them out on a job.
Name: The Mean Market

Description: Channel the power of the Jade Golems. These minions get stronger for each one you play, so play as many as you can!
Name: The Lotus’ Golems

Description: The Kabal traffic in some dark magics. Unleash your darker side and summon some of the most evil demons this side of Azeroth.
Name: Demons of the Kabal

Description: Bolster your armies with the innumerable minions of the Old Gods. Swarm the board with smaller minions to overwhelm your opponent.
Name: Ancient Hordes

Description: The pirates are the closest thing to legitimate trade you’ll get in Gadgetzan. Dock your ship and let loose a tide of piracy to rush down your opponent!
Name: Gadgetzan Dockside

Description: Kazakus has always had a soft spot for Dragons. Combine his potions and their fiery might to overwhelm your opponents!
Name: Hidden Dragon

Description: Those of you not scared of beasts have clearly never seen one with tons of weapons attached. Suit up your beasts and get ‘em out there!
Name: Band of Beasts

Description: The greatest leaders in the Kabal combine their powers into a mixture of fury! Your deck has only one of each card so your leaders can unleash their full power!
Name: Kabalist Mixology

Description: Shields up!  You are forging Sulfuras but need more time. Use Taunt minions to protect your hero until you seize the legendary hammer and SWAT SOME INSECTS!
Name: Guarding the Shard

Description: The elements have come to your aid!  Call upon hordes of elementals, create mighty storms, and crush all who stand in your path…
Name: Storm, Earth, and Fire

Description: Pirates are searching the ice caverns of Un’goro for hidden treasure. Play the same minion multiple times and unearth the Crystal Core to empower the rest of your scoundrels!
Name: The Dig

Description: Who really wants small minions? Make them mighty and dinosized!  Cast spells on your small minions to power the crystals and unleash the mighty Galvadon.
Name: Primordial Blessings

Description: Summon forth a glorious host of Deathrattle minions to receive the Light’s ultimate boon.
Name: Awakenings

Description: Dragons and tigers and dinos, oh my! Grow quickly and summon big dinosaurs to draw out Barnabus to stomp your opponent.
Name: Might of the Dino King

Description: The chaotic fire elementals hunger for destruction!  Harness their power to melt your opponent’s minions away.
Name: Flames of the Phoenix

Description: Set down your bow, and claim the Dinomancer title.  Summon beasts and then supersize them using your new hero power!
Name: Dinomancer

Description: Discard your cards into the volatile Nether Portal.  Tear open the rift and unlock a limitless legion of imps!
Name: Feed the Void

Description: Control your opponent... with Weapons
Name: The Rock

Description: Fast and fierce, this deck hates weapons!
Name: Fierce Forest

Description: Don't mess with the master of secrets.
Name: Spy Stalker

Description: No one can unravel your secrets. Except the Hunter.
Name: Secret Magus

Description: Fast. Secrets. Dragons. Good luck!
Name: Mysterious e-SCALE-ation

Description: Slow to start, but inspirational to behold.
Name: Unbreakable Inspiration

Description: Fast miracle rogue. Loves weapons and Yogg-Saron.
Name: The Saint

Description: Blast away your opponent's secrets!
Name: Totems Hate Secrets

Description: You love death and sort of hate weapons.
Name: Death Becomes Your Foes

Description: True power comes at a price. Sacrifice your own minions to feed your others and embrace the darkness of the San'layn.
Name: Merciless Sacrifice

Description: Your minions are ready and willing to do your bidding and whatever it takes to succeed. Deal damage to your own minions and finish the job as Scourgelord Garrosh, cleaving a path to victory with Shadowmourne.
Name: No Pain, No Gain

Description: Corrupt the wilds and disrupt the natural order! Control a swarm of poisonous spiders, scarabs, and big Taunt minions to whittle your opponent down and show them that none can withstand the might of the Scourge.
Name: Pestilence

Description: The Void shall burn you! Use the power of the Light to accumulate fuel with Lyra the Sunshard. Then unleash the dark power of Shadowreaper Anduin and your army of spell damage minions and spells.
Name: Shadowreaper's Revenge

Description: Take the fight to the Lich King and go offensive with your Divine Shield minions! Wield the power of the divine to bolster your minions and weapons in the fight against evil.
Name: Shields of the Light

Description: Valeera and Aya Blackpaw team up to wreak havoc on their foes. Command your army of Deathrattle and Jade minions to gain early tempo and finish off your opponent with Valeera the Hollow and N'Zoth, the Corruptor.
Name: Jades of Death

Description: Control the elements of the frost and stop your opponent cold in their tracks. Freeze the blood in your enemies' veins and use ice to bolster your own minions!
Name: Remorseless Winter

Description: Frost Lich Jaina is summoning elementals to do her bidding and is adding a frosty touch. Mix the power of fiery and frosty elementals to burn and freeze your foes.
Name: Fire and Ice

Description: Deathstalker Rexxar commands a horde of Deathrattle minions. Send your minions to die and raise them from their graves. Finish off your foe by stitching together beasts and forming grotesque Zombeasts.
Name: The Eternal Hunt

Description: In this jungle lurks giant beasts and even darker things...
Name: Rumble in the Jungle

Description: Release a stampede of beasts while hunting for the Marsh Queen!
Name: Unleash the Beasts

Description: Guard your secrets and unleash elemental fury!
Name: Elemental Secrets

Description: Bend the Light to your will, while you unleash the Apocalypse!
Name: Dark Light

Description: Bash your opponent with weapons
Name: The Rock

Description: Slow to start, but inspirational to behold.
Name: Unbreakable Inspiration

Description: Fast miracle rogue who worships Yogg-Saron.
Name: The Acolyte

Description: Blast away your opponent's secrets!
Name: Totems Hate Secrets

Description: Summon monstrous demons and burn away the enemy's weapons
Name: Death Becomes Your Foes

Description: Your Silver Hand Recruits are ready for action! Call upon the power of your eager recruits. They've been training heavily and are ready to prove their worth and Level Up! on the battlefield.
Name: Call to Arms

Description: Recruit the mighty creatures of the dungeon to your cause! Clone your party and overwhelm your foes with powerful Deathrattle effects.
Name: Out of the Woods

Description: Even though your deck has no minions, you'll never truly be alone. Set deadly traps and summon animal allies until you're ready to finish off your foes with Rhok'delar!
Name: I Hunt Alone

Description: Mage is all about big, flashy spells. But what kind of minions do you want in a deck like that? Ones that give you MORE spells! Once you've had your fill of slinging magic, use Dragoncaller Alanna to summon the fury of the mighty Red Dragonflight!
Name: Spells are fun, SO FUN!

Description: Harness the power of the Dragon Soul to strike fear into your opponent’s heart. Unleash the twilight dragons upon your foes, leaving you and your hoard of loot alone.
Name: Dragon's Call

Description: Sonya Shadowdancer has signed a secret pact with the Fal'dorei. Help your new allies swarm the battlefield again and again until your enemy is no more.
Name: Shrouded in Secrecy

Description: Winds, obey my command! Bless your simple totems with enchantments to keep them alive. Once the ritual is complete, summon Al'Akir the Windlord to crush your foes!
Name: Totemic Call

Description: Bloodreaver Gul'dan has acquired a weapon of insurmountable power and entered into a dark pact to wield it. Do you dare unlock the power of the Skull of the Man'ari and the demons that serve it?
Name: The Dark Pact

Description: Outlast your opponents in this war of attrition. Why just wear armor when you can fight with it?! Keep your armor high and finish the game with an army of Mithril Golems.
Name: Armor Up!

Description: Take advantage of card advantage with effects that become more powerful with lots of cards in hand. Overwhelm enemies with a constant stream of minions!
Name: Victory at Hand

Description: The denizens of the marsh love to be in the presence of death. Join their hunt and your opponents will fall prey to the monsters of the Witchwood!
Name: Dragons of the Swamp

Description: The Book of Specters contains tales of many monsters. None are more terrifying than the heartless Elementals, ready to devour any who cross their path.
Name: Book of Specters

Description: Genn Greymane joins forces with the Silver Hand, using only even-Cost cards to purge Gilneas of the Witchwood's encroaching evils.
Name: Greymane's Alliance

Description: Baku's presence infuses your Hero Power with moonlight in this deck of only odd-Cost cards. Keep your minions healthy, then empower them!
Name: Moonlight Vigil

Description: The Witchwood is no place to travel alone... echoes of past tragedies linger in the air, threatening to drive mad any who overstay their welcome.
Name: Ghostly Echoes

Description: The Witchwood stirs, awoken by the magics of Hagatha herself! Build up powerful Battlecry effects, then repeat them with the horrifying Shudderwock.
Name: Witchwood Awoken

Description: Power may come at a price, but seeing your enemies cower before you is worth any cost. Unleash the very darkness of the Witchwood!
Name: Witch's Bargain

Description: Your minions are looking for a fight, and they know how to win. Punish your opponent's every move and smash your way to an overwhelming victory!
Name: Rush In!

Description: Tank Up with this deck of all odd-Cost cards, Taunt your opponents as they run out of resources, then blast them with the power of Ragnaros himself!
Name: The Gilneas Armory

Description: Dr. Boom's Mech factory is developing DEADLY technology. (Dr. Boom's Guarantee: Probably more deadly for your opponent!)
Name: The Boomsday Project

Description: The scientific field of study favored by Warlocks is all about experimenting on Demons and ghosts. Don't worry, they won't mind... probably.
Name: Demonology Lab

Description: The clock is ticking. Reach 10 Mana Crystals to unlock the power of the Omega Project and bring doom to any who stand in your way!
Name: The Omega Project

Description: "Borrow" ideas from your opponent by generating cards from their class, then use them for profit. Who knew being a scientist was so easy?!
Name: Stolen Research

Description: Myra Rotspring is studying the effects of Necrium and has nicknamed it "Artificial Death." Test subjects say it feels just like the real thing!
Name: The Necrium Trials

Description: Build a custom Mech army! Magnetic Mechs combine to create all new ways to smash your opponent.
Name: Kangor's Endless Army

Description: The Witchwood stirs, awoken by the magics of Hagatha herself! Your powerful spells and minions assure you maintain complete control of the battlefield.
Name: Witchwood Awoken

Description: The Netherstorm is home to fearsome Elementals. Harness their power and bring destruction to your foes at lightning speed!
Name: The Storm Bringer

Description: Have a bomb? Want to attach another bomb, strap on some rockets, then watch everything explode? Then Boommaster Flark has a deck for you!
Name: Flark's Fireworks

Description: Teach the trees to fight back! Cultivate an army of Treants that will tear asunder any who would dare loot and plunder.
Name: Trees Are Friends

Description: Zerek, Master Cloner will conduct any experiment necessary to achieve immortality. Copy Deathrattle minions and discover the secret for yourself!
Name: Quest For Immortality

Description: Priest Scientists are hard at work discovering how to hit someone really, really hard. Buff up a minion and share your findings - with your opponent!
Name: Awesome Augmentation

Description: Mages have learned how to wield the very power of the stars. Combine Spell Damage with devastating effects to erase your enemies from existence!
Name: Shooting Stars

Description: Take matters into your own hands! Improve your hero's Attack to enable Gonk's Raptors to take over the battle.
Name: Feral Frenzy

Description: Boost the power of your beasts with the Spirit of the Lynx. Swarm the board early, then get even more beasts with the help of Halazzi!
Name: Animal Instincts

Description: The Dragonhawks LOVE fire! Upgrade your hero power for even MORE FIRE! Set enough things on fire and you might even summon the Firelord himself...
Name: Power of the Dragonhawk

Description: Shirvallah's Tigers say they're the strongest fighters in Stranglethorn. Enhance your minions with powerful spells to test their might.
Name: Shirvallah's Chosen

Description: Bwonsamdi's Zombies don't stay dead for long. Shuffle your fallen minions into your deck with Spirit of the Dead, then power them up with Surrender to Madness!
Name: Surrender to Madness

Description: The Sharkfin Crew has bribed Genn Greymane to join their cause. Raid the board with your pirates and blow your opponent out of the water with Cannon Barrage.
Name: Cursed Crew

Description: Da Frogs are big into voodoo, 'mon. Embrace your darker side and evolve your minions for powerful and unpredictable results!
Name: Big Bad Voodoo

Description: The trolls will sacrifice just about anything to win. Manipulate your discard effects to unlock extra power and take over the game!
Name: Reckless Ritual

Description: War Master Voone is building an army of dragons to take the Rumble by storm. Turn your foes to ashes with their powerful battlecry effects!
Name: Wings of War

Description: Swarm the board with sacrificial minions to offer to the Spirit of the Bat. End the game by unleashing the mad god Hir'eek upon your opponent!
Name: Hir'eek's Offering

Description: Rafaam's imps are swarming the streets of Dalaran. Summon the Legion to unlock the power of the largest, mightiest imps!

Description: Justice demands an upgraded hero power! With the help of Sir Finley and Zephrys, you'll be sure to have the perfect tools to fight EVIL.

Description: Reno Jackson has made some interesting discoveries in Uldum. Take advantage of his latest find and obliterate your opponent's board!

Description: Amplify the Light itself in this Holy-themed Quest deck. Empower your minions and utilize your healing to keep them in the fight!
